docs.lead_paragraph: An airstrike near the site of a suspected gas attack in Syria killed at least 10 civilians Wednesday, as U.S. Secretary of State John Kerry and Russian Foreign Minister Sergey Lavrov agreed to meet this week for extended discussions on ending the 5-year-old civil war.

docs.lead_paragraph: The election of Waseem Akhtar to lead the city of 22 million comes as his Muttahida Qaumi Movement and its exiled leader are under fire from Pakistan’s military.
docs.abstract: Karachi, Pakistan, Mayor Waseem Akhtar wins reelection despite having been imprisoned since July on charges including incitement of citywide riots in May 2007; Akhtar's party Muttahida Qaumi Movement, or MQM, has for decades led violent city through combination of wiles and intimidation, but in 2013 it became subject of military crackdown.

headline.main: New Karachi Mayor Gets Daytrip From Prison to Be Sworn In
headline.print_headline: Pakistani Inmate Faces Charges and New Duties as Mayor of Chaotic Karachi

byline.contributor: Zia ur-Rehman reported from Karachi, and Salman Masood from Islamabad, Pakistan.
byline.original: By ZIA ur-REHMAN and SALMAN MASOOD

docs.lead_paragraph: Almost none of the governor’s seasoned staff members are helping Mr. Trump in Ohio, which no candidate since 1964 has lost and still won the White House.
docs.abstract: Almost none of Republican Gov John Kasich's senior political staffers have offered their services to Donald Trump in his battle against Hillary Clinton in Ohio; refusals follow bitter feud between Kasich and Trump that boiled over during nominating convention in Cleveland; strategists say Trump's tough  chances of success in Ohio rest more on his campaign's fundamental structural problems than on lack of Kasich's operatives.

headline.main: Donald Trump’s Feud With John Kasich May Haunt Him in Ohio
headline.print_headline: In Must-Win Ohio, Trump’s Feud With Kasich Has Come Back to Haunt Him
